aboutPageWhoWeAreContent.en-US:
Cialfo started in 2016 with one mission: to increase transparency and accessibility of college information. 

Our team is made up of former college counselors, educators, and technology professionals working to change how the world approaches post-secondary education. And our platform emerges from the real world experiences of those we serve, whether theyre a devoted counselor or a steadfast principal.

aboutPageBusinessAdvisorBlurb.en-US: Originally from New York and Northern Virginia, Karen graduated from Columbia University with a B.S. in Applied Mathematics. Not ready to leave academia, she worked in the Undergraduate Admissions at both Dartmouth College and Columbia University.  While at Columbia, she completed her M.A. in Higher and Postsecondary Education followed by a Certificate Program in International Counseling at Lehigh University. Karen made the transition to the other side of the desk and began university counseling at the Potomac School, outside Washington, DC.  With an avid love of travel and adventure, Karen found she was spending every summer exploring new countries and cultures, which influenced her decision to move to Belgium to join the International School of Brussels counseling team. Karen is currently IB/AP Coordinator at International School Manila.

bulletPoint.en-US: Give teachers their own portals so they can manage their document overview
bulletPoint.zh-CN: Give teachers their own portals so they can manage their document overview

aboutPageBusinessAdvisorBlurb.en-US: Trevor worked for several years at International School Manila where he served as High School Counselor and Department Head of Counseling PK-12. Trevor earned a Bachelor of Education from McGill University, a Masters degree in Educational Counseling, and a Masters of Educational Leadership degree. He was formerly VP of Finance as well as a VP of Communications and Technology for the Overseas Association of College Admission Counseling (OACAC).

With over 30 years of experience in college admissions and financial aid, Katy was a past president of the National Association for College Admission Counseling (NACAC) as well as the Western Association for College Admission Counseling (WACAC). Katy is an instructor at the UC Berkeley and UCLA Extension College Counseling Certificate Programs and currently serves the Director of College Counseling at Bellarmine College Preparatory.

Peggy Hock received both her bachelors and Ph.D. degrees in psychology from Columbia University. She was an assistant professor of psychology at Dartmouth College and a research scientist at Stanford University, has been the director of college counseling at three San Francisco Bay area private high schools, and is currently an instructor in the UC Berkeley College Counseling Certificate Program. She is a past-president of the Western Association for College Admissions Counseling.

Michelle is currently in her sixth year in the University Counseling Office at Hisar School. Before transitioning to university counseling, she was on the international admissions team at Boston University for thirteen years. Michelle also worked in the school counseling office at Colegio Nueva Granada in Bogota, Colombia for a year after completing her Masters Degree in Higher Education Administration at Boston University in 1999.

As the President of Taylor's Education Group, former Executive Vice President at Blackboard, and former Managing Director of the Nobel Education Network, Karl has deep experience in building and scaling education technology companies. His expertise spans across business development, strategy, and operations roles at Nobel Education Network, Pearson, Blackboard, Campus Direct and The Princeton Review.

Bob Patterson is currently the CEO of BE Education. At Chegg, Bob was previously Vice President of Student Success and later a Chegg Foundation Board Member. He brings a deep expertise in college admissions from his experience in admissions offices at Stanford University, UC Berkeley, and UNC Chapel Hill. Bob also served as an elected delegate on the National Association of College Admission Counseling (NACAC).

homePageHeaderTitle.en-US: Top performing principals use Cialfo to manage their schools

homePageHeaderBlurb.en-US: Get unparalleled access into your data. Cialfo empowers data-driven principals and administrators to analyze, visualize, and share reports. Want to know your application history over the last 10 years or trends in college destinations? Now you can.

homePageSchoolTestimonialsTitle.en-US: The best international schools trust Cialfo

homePageFeaturesSendDocumentBlurb.en-US: Can your school or district measure key college counseling success metrics? Track college outcomes and report results in an easily exportable spreadsheet. Use Reports to discover application histories, measure student success based on ethnicity or gender, and forecast college application trends.

homePageFeaturesLeverageTitle.en-US: One platform for teachers, counselors, students, and parents

homePageFeaturesLeverageBlurb.en-US: When you subscribe to Cialfo, you only pay for your graduating class. All other students receive access to Cialfo so college prep can begin early. Guardians and parents can track their childs college application process with separate logins, while teachers use Teacher Accounts to submit and manage letters of recommendation.

aboutPageBusinessAdvisorBlurb.en-US: As Head of College Counseling at Aditya Birla World Academy, Sonia brings almost 14 years of experience to our board. Sonia holds a Doctorate of Psychology from the Maharastra University,  a Graduate Certificate in College Counselling from UCLA & a Certificate in College Admissions from  Harvard Summer Institute at Harvard University.

As Head of University Guidance at YCIS, John brings 15 years of education to Cialfo's advisory board. John was formerly Director of Counseling at International Bilingual School at Hsinchu Science Park, and holds an MEd in Independent School Leadership as well as an MA in Educational Leadership from Teachers College of Columbia University.

Prior to joining Dhirubhai Ambani International School, Barry was a college counselor at the American International School of Lagos and International School of Beijing. Barry holds an MEd in School Counseling from University of Southern Queensland and currently serves as Deputy Head of Secondary at Oberoi International School.

mainTitleText.en-US: Tools for comprehensive career and college counseling

text1.en-US: Dig into a rich database of over 10,000 post-secondary schools worldwide. Explore the past acceptances, essay prompts, and statistics that make up a school on Cialfo, then shortlist or longlist them.

text2.en-US: Show your work and drill down into your data to understand what programs are working and which factors affect application results. Analyze class profiles, student data, expected outcome, matriculation rates, and more, then export a PDF for simple sharing.

text3.en-US: Send electronic documents like transcripts and letters of recommendation quickly with cDocs. Integrated with Parchment and The Common Application, cDocs is a simpler way to send and monitor documents.

text4.en-US: Cialfos intelligent Reach/Target/Likely algorithm takes into account a students personal profile and the schools historical data before creating a personalized recommendation. And, of course: the counselor can always, at any time, override it.

text5.en-US: Organize and manage college representative visits or college fairs without the hassle. Look up the details, send broadcast announcements to students, and manage registrations and deadlines  all on one page.

text6.en-US: Send assessments and track completion status on a simple dashboard. Assign different types of assessments for different groups of students. Both you and your student receive a copy of the results for discussion.

text1.en-US: Build task lists made up of individual tasks, then assign them to students. Want to take it up a notch? Cialfo can automatically assign task lists to students matching pre-set criteria like Canada Applications, current grade K10.

text2.en-US: Imagine if each time a student shortlisted a college, they immediately received a series of tasks to complete with no effort on your part. With Application Configs, you simply set the assignment criteria, create the tasks, and let Cialfo work.

text3.en-US: However you work, Cialfo adapts to it. Dont want your students to edit college lists? Sure. Want to turn off the shortlisting algorithm? No problem. Cialfo is wonderfully flexible, so you can truly make it your own.

text4.en-US: Send announcements and broadcast messages to your students, their guardians, or fellow colleagues. Choose how they receive the broadcast: via SMS, email, in-app message, or all three.

text5.en-US: Students request recommendations from teachers, who manage requests and write recommendations. Counselors track overall statuses of LoRs, provide helpful nudges, and deliver them to colleges.

text6.en-US: Draft notes before, during, or after a meeting. Choose whether to share it with the student, with colleagues, or simply keep it to yourself.
